Section 1:
Act 840 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H4/3/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1870
4
5 By: Representative Wing
6 By: Senator M. McKee
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT CONCERNING VOTER REGISTRATION LISTS; TO ALLOW
10 THE SECRETARY OF STATE TO PROVIDE A VOTER
11 REGISTRATION LIST TO FEDERAL COURTS; AND FOR OTHER
12 PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 CONCERNING VOTER REGISTRATION LISTS; AND
17 TO ALLOW THE SECRETARY OF STATE TO
18 PROVIDE A VOTER REGISTRATION LIST TO
19 FEDERAL COURTS.
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 7, Chapter 1, Subchapter 1, is amended
24 to add an additional section to read as follows:
25 7-1-116. Voter registration lists provided to federal courts.
26 (a) The Secretary of State may provide a voter registration list to a
27 federal court for purposes of selecting jurors on the condition that the
28 federal court jury coordinator provides notice to the Secretary of State
29 regarding an ineligible or potentially ineligible voter under subsection (b)
30 of this section.
31 (b)(1) The notice under subsection (a) of this section shall include
32 a list of each person disqualified or potentially disqualified as a
33 prospective juror from jury service due to the prospective juror being:
34 (A) A noncitizen of the United States;
35 (B) Convicted of a felony;
36 (C) Deceased;
*SSS276*
04-03-2025 11:23:32 SSS276
As Engrossed: H4/3/25 HB1870
1 (D) A nonresident of this state; or
2 (E) A nonresident of the county.
3 (2) The notice under subsection (a) of this section shall
4 include the following information for each disqualified juror:
5 (A) The full name of the disqualified juror;
6 (B) Current and prior addresses, if any;
7 (C) Telephone number, if available;
8 (D) Date of birth; and
9 (E) The reason the prospective juror was disqualified.
10 (3) The federal court jury coordinator may provide additional
11 documentation showing the person's disqualification under subsection (b) of
12 this section with the notice submitted to the Secretary of State.
13 (c)(1) The notice prepared under subsection (a) of this section shall
14 be sent to the Secretary of State according to the jury summons cycle used by
15 the federal district court clerk.
16 (2) Subdivision (c)(1) of this section does not prevent the
17 notice from being sent more frequently.
18 (3) The notice under subsection (a) of this section may be
19 provided to the Secretary of State by:
20 (A) Mail;
21 (B) Facsimile transmission; or
22 (C) Email.
23 (d)(1) After verifying that the person disqualified or potentially
24 disqualified as a prospective juror is a registered voter but is ineligible
25 to be a voter under Arkansas law, the Secretary of State shall forward the
26 information to the county clerk where the voter is registered.
27 (2) The county clerk shall follow the procedures to remove the
28 voter from the voter registration list under Arkansas Constitution, Amendment
29 51, ยง 11.
30
